This directory houses various versions of the updated Secure Note
application. All JavaScript code is accumulated into a single source
file.

You may have to create the SNote/Blobs/ directory and change its owner
to www-data (for an Apache web server on Linux at least).

The test.php page can be loaded with a parameter string as follows to
choose which version to run.

http://mwwidgets/test.php?script=mwwidgets.jam.js&policy=policy.js


Original README notes from MIT-LL:

KNOWN ATTACKS

* XSS - since the widget id read from the wiki text is used as the id of
the div added for the widget without proper validation, including
javascript in the widget id can result in a cross-site scripting attack.
